Why We Love Fear And Game of Thrones And the much loved...

为什么我们爱恐惧、权力的游戏，以及许多被爱的事物……

![](media/15065989759397/15065992936344.jpg)

Jon Snow or Aegon Targaryen whatever, among the most fearless characters throughout the fictional universe. 

We are used to horrible things happening in Game of Thrones, whether it’s Ned Stark‘s head getting chopped off in “Baelor,” Jon Snow being stabbed to death by the Night’s Watch in “Mother’s Mercy,” or the ultimate heartbreaker, the Red Wedding.

Ugh.

Can you still feel this unpleasant feeling when I mention these?

We call that "Observational fear”.

Jon Snow或者Aegon Targaryen，无论在虚构宇宙中最无畏的人物中。

我们习惯于在权力游戏中发生的可怕事件，无论是Ned Stark在“Baelor”中被砍掉的头，Jon Snow被“The Mother's Mercy”的夜表刺死，还是终极的伤心者，Red 婚礼。

当我提到这些时，你还能感觉到这种不愉快的感觉吗？

我们称之为“观察恐惧”。

![](media/15065989759397/15065993474096.jpg)


## Question 1: What happened in the brain when we watch these episodes?

Warning: the following talk occasionally contains pictures make you feel unpleasant and neuroscience terminologies make you feel boring (which I don’t care either way).

问题1：当我们观看这些剧集时，大脑发生了什么事？

警告：下面的谈话偶尔会包含图片让你感到不愉快，神经科学术语使你感到无聊（虽然我不是很在意这一点）。

![](media/15065989759397/15065993717123.jpg)


![](media/15065989759397/15065993746885.jpg)


This screenshot is horrible to most of us, especially to Kit Harington — who plays Snow, he said he had to face his worst fear while filming 'Battle of the Bastards’.

这个屏幕截图对我们大多数人来说是可怕的，特别是对于扮演Snow的Kit Harington，他说他在拍摄“Battle of the Bastards”时不得不面对最糟糕的恐惧。

![](media/15065989759397/15065993960067.jpg)


Fear of being killed or suffocation.

Fear is an evolutionarily conserved survival response triggered by imminent threats that evokes rapid defensive responses of immobility, attack, or escape, accompanied by hormonal and autonomic changes in preparation for the behavioral response.

In humans, there may also be accompanying feelings of dread and/or despair. These behavioral changes are rapidly engaged and abate once the threat has ended.

In humans, it describes a range of disorders such as generalized anxiety disorder, panic disorder, PTSD, and social affective disorder.

害怕被杀或窒息。

恐惧是由即将来临的威胁触发的进化保守的生存反应，引发不动，攻击或逃跑的快速防御反应，伴随着激素和自主变化，为行为反应做准备。

在人类中，也可能伴随着恐惧和/或绝望的感觉。 一旦威胁已经结束，这些行为变化就会迅速消失。

在人类中，它描述了一系列疾病，如广泛性焦虑症，恐慌症，PTSD和社会情感障碍。

![](media/15065989759397/15065995116313.jpg)

